      "title": "[Boing Boing] Why speaking your journal beats typing it",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/speaking_into_phone.jpg?fit=1200%2C798&quality=60&ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/18/why-speaking-your-journal-beats-typing-it.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Why speaking your journal beats typing it\"><img alt=\"Kateryna Onyshchuk/shutterstock.com\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"798\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/speaking_into_phone.jpg?fit=1200%2C798&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1200\" /></a><p>Mohsen Askari describes a daily practice <a href=\"https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-write-yourself-every-day\">in Psyche</a> that takes about six minutes: speak into voice-to-text about whatever is happening in your inner life. Don't edit the transcript. Later, read it back as if it belongs to a character in a story — \"who is this person today?\" &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/18/why-speaking-your-journal-beats-typing-it.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/18/why-speaking-your-journal-beats-typing-it.html\">Why speaking your journal beats typing it</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
